TextBody:
Hi Joel,

The first thing I noticed is that the DPI log file is missing, this tells me that DPI is not enabled based on the logs.
Also saw that there are no allowlists loaded for the policy. This could be a result of the DPI not being seen as enabled, or the allowlists were not saved.
I suggest removing the allowlists from the policy, save, then editing again, re-adding the allowlists you had previously, and save.
After that, try doing the same thing with Deep Packet Inspection for the computer we collected logs for.

If you are still having the same issue, we need to set up another meeting, but this time we will need to have access to a computer where we can reproduce the issue and try to resolve it. Even a test computer you might have were you can reproduce the issue.

Thank you,
Eduard Nut
